title: Patsy.Cline.Video.Collection1
description:
This torrent is an augmentation of torrent #11037999 wherein I explained that most of this collection of Patsy Cline videos had been clipped out of a DVD release of a television documentary entitled "Patsy Cline: Sweet Dreams Still" (IMDB: tt0780580). 

The reason why I had these performances as separate tracks is also something I explained at torrent #11037999 (that's @ piratebay) which, much to my surprise, has been quite a popular little torrent - quite a bit more popular than I'd expected! 

Ã¢â‚¬Â¦ well I guess I wouldn't have been very surprised if I'd actually gone online looking specifically for Patsy Cline videos, the plenitude of which is too painfully small to be worthy of mention.

[RANT]
By my estimation, the reason for this lack of PC content can only be put down to corporate avarice because it's clear from the quality of some of these recordings, that said content exists somewhere in some archive but has obviously never been made publicly available in full.

As an example, take this famous "Ranch Party" episode, which you can find IN FULL (guests: Carl Perkins, Johnny Cash and Patsy Cline) and at the SUPER-DUPER HIGH RESOLUTION of ~292x220 and a whopping VBPS of FIVE HUNDRED THOUSAND bytes per second! (ie. video data rate = 500 kbps) over at archive org. All of that, FOR FREE!

Well a magnifying glass isn't going to help you with that quality of video. The best way to view it is at it's normal size or else it becomes so blurred you can't make out that there are people in there.

But as you can see from video #3 (I've Loved And Lost Again) that that episode is available somewhere in full quality both audio and video. It is simply too valuable for anyone to admit they have a copy and be forced to make it public.
[/RANT]

Anyway, I added 6 more tracks that I could scrape out of YouTube, and that appears to be all there is besides a few blurred "flashing's of light" that are said to be video recordings of Patsy Cline. Of these extra 6, one had to be re-encoded so that I could make a "left cut" (if you've done any video editing you know what I mean) and two were rescaled and in two cases I had to do some audio editing (noise removal and normalization).

So here is the track list as it now stands:

Once again, enjoy!
